ce:section.ce:para:
Hyaluronic acid modified carbon dots were synthesized with PEI, citric acid and hyaluronic acid as starting materials in mild conditions within 1 h according to our previous publication [24]. The element analysis result showed that N was detected, suggesting PEI and HA residuals remained on the surface of carbon dots. Intermediate product HA-CD-p-CBA was synthesized by conjugating p-CBA to HA-CD through an amide bond. Then, DOX was conjugated to the intermediate HA-CD-p-CBA to synthesize DOX@HA-CD by forming acid-sensitive imine bond between the amine group in DOX and the aldehyde group in p-CBA. Boc-anhydride was widely used in introducing the tert-butoxycarbonyl (BOC) to amine, which converted amines into carbomates [28]. To synthesize and optimise the self-assembled SA-DOX@HA-CD different amount of BOC/methanol solution was added into DOX@HA-CD and incubated for 4 h (Scheme 1
                        ). The chemical structures of different products were certified by 1H-NMR spectra (Fig. 1
                        A-B). In the HA-CD spectrum, chemical shift at 1.93 ppm belonged to the characteristic peaks of HA and 2.4-2.8 ppm referred to protons on the -CH2N- of PEI. The chemical shift at 7.79 and 7.58 ppm is of typical benzene ring indicating that p-CBA was conjugated with HA-CD v. For DOX@HA-CD, two characteristic peaks at 3.50 and 1.09 and 3.50 ppm were assigned to -OCH3 of benzene of DOX and -CH3 of pyranose ring, separately.
